{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "Study of energy and system size fluctuations of identified hadrons is one of the key goals of NA61/SHINE at the CERN SPS. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Results may allow to discover the critical point (CP) of strongly interacting matter as well as to uncover properties of the onset of deconfinement (OD). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "But fluctuations exhibit numerous other sources starting from most basic ones like volume effects and conservation laws.",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "NA49 seems to observe fluctuations related to CP in collisions of medium size nuclei at top SPS energy. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "However, this result will remain inconclusive until systematic data on energy and system size dependence will be available. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Moreover, fluctuations in p+p as well as in Pb+Pb interactions should be better understood.",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "In this contribution results on multiplicity fluctuations of identified hadrons in p+p interactions at the CERN SPS energies will be presented. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The NA61 data will be compared with the corresponding results from central Pb+Pb collisions of NA49 in the common acceptance region of both experiments. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Moreover, predictions of models (EPOS, UrQMD and HSD) for both reactions will be tested.",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Introduction",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "It is a well established fact that matter exists in different states. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "One of the most important goals of heavy-ion collision (HIC) experiments is to study the phase diagram of strongly interacting matter by finding possible phase boundaries and establishing their properties. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "In particular, high energy HIC experiments want to study the deconfined matter (QGP) and the transition between QGP and confined hadrons. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The NA61/SHINE experiment [1] is a fixed target experiment in the European Organization for Nuclear Research (CERN) at the Super Proton Synchrotron (SPS). ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 26,
                    "end": 29,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
