                    "start": 4,
                    "end": 14,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "NA61/SHINE",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The study of energy and system size dependence of fluctuations of identified hadrons is one of the goals of the NA61/SHINE ion program. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 112,
                    "end": 123,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "NA61/SHINE",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The aim of this program is to search for the critical point (CP) [2] of strongly interacting matter as well as to uncover properties of the onset of deconfinement (OD) [3,4]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 65,
                    "end": 68,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 168,
                    "end": 171,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 171,
                    "end": 173,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "4]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The predecessor of NA61/SHINE, the NA49 experiment [5] seems to observe fluctuations possibly related to the CP in collisions of medium size nuclei at the top energy of SPS [6]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 51,
                    "end": 54,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[5]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 173,
                    "end": 176,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "[6]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 19,
                    "end": 29,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "NA61/SHINE",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "However, measured fluctuations are affected by numerous effects not related to CP or OD like volume fluctuations and conservation laws. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Thus, this result will remain inconclusive until systematic data on energy and system size dependence will be available. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "These data are being recorded and analysed by NA61/SHINE. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 46,
                    "end": 56,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "NA61/SHINE",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The energy dependence of mean multiplicity of identified charged (left) and positively charged (right) hadrons in p+p interactions in the acceptance used for the fluctuation analysis.",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "NA61/SHINE identified hadron fluctuation studies",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Second moments of identified hadron multiplicity distributions were obtained using the identity method [7,8,9]. ",
            "section": "NA61/SHINE identified hadron fluctuation studies",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 103,
                    "end": 106,
