        {
            "text": "Model predictions are presented for the NA61/SHINE acceptance.",
            "section": "NA61/SHINE identified hadron fluctuation studies",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "probably connected with the strangeness conservation, which leads to a correlation between the K + and K \u2212 productions. ",
            "section": "NA61/SHINE identified hadron fluctuation studies",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "It is supported by the fact that \u03c9 K + < \u03c9 K [15]. ",
            "section": "NA61/SHINE identified hadron fluctuation studies",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 45,
                    "end": 49,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b14",
                    "text": "[15]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "It should be underlined that the influence of a specific charge conservation on the scaled variance depends on the volume of the system, mean number and mass of charge carriers, and the fraction of measured particles and anti-particles. ",
            "section": "NA61/SHINE identified hadron fluctuation studies",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Measured quantities are approximately reproduced by the EPOS [16,17], UrQMD [18,19] and HSD [20,21,22] models. ",
            "section": "NA61/SHINE identified hadron fluctuation studies",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
