        {
            "text": "In order to compare results for p+p and 3.5% of most central Pb+Pb collisions , the strongly intensive measure, [23,10], defined for two hadron types, i and j, was chosen,",
            "section": "NA61/SHINE identified hadron fluctuation studies",
